summary:
The Security Council:
- Reaffirms all previous resolutions on Western Sahara, particularly 1108 (1997), 1292 (2000), 1301 (2000), 1309 (2000), and 1308 (2000);
- Recalls principles from the Convention on the Safety of UN and Associated Personnel;
- Welcomes the Secretary-General's report (S/2000/1029) and supports the Personal Envoy's role;
- Reiterates support for MINURSO's efforts to implement the Settlement Plan for a free, fair, and impartial referendum;
- Notes remaining fundamental differences between parties on the Settlement Plan;
- Decides to extend MINURSO's mandate until 28 February 2001, expecting parties to work towards resolving disputes under the Personal Envoy's auspices;
- Requests the Secretary-General to assess the situation before the mandate ends;
- Decides to remain seized of the matter.
